  "body": "In ```interpreter.go``` ```Run()```, ```gasCost()``` is called. For some opcodes, such as ```CALL```, ```DELEGATECALL```, ```STATICCALL```, ```CALLCODE```, this causes the stack to be altered.\r\n\r\nAs a result, the subsequent ```CaptureState()``` call does not log the correct stack.\r\n\r\nMy solution is to make a copy of ```stack``` in ```oldStack``` before ```gasCost()``` is called, and later log ```oldStack``` with ```CaptureState()```.\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\t\tif !in.cfg.DisableGasMetering {\r\n                       ...\r\n                       ...\r\n                       /* stack altered in gasCost */\r\n\t\t\tcost, err = operation.gasCost(in.gasTable, in.evm, contract, stack, mem, memorySize)\r\n                       ...\r\n                       ...\r\n\t\t}\r\n               ...\r\n               ...\r\n\t\tif in.cfg.Debug {\r\n                        /* altered stack logged here */\r\n\t\t\tin.cfg.Tracer.CaptureState(in.evm, pc, op, gasCopy, cost, mem, stackCopy, contract, in.evm.depth, err)\r\n\t\t\tlogged = true\r\n}\r\n```",
